*Usage note: ''This masculine word is irregular. '''Ljudi''' (people, men) is the plural form of the singular word '''čovjek''' (man).  Because of the existence of dual grammatical numbers in Bosnian, the dual form (the form for 2, 3, and 4) is '''čovjeka'''.  The dual numbers also apply to any higher numbers ending in 2, 3, and 4, such as 22, 23, and 24.''
*:Example of dual numbers:  ''Dva čovjeka su išla cestom.'' (''Two men walked down the street.'')
*:Example of plural:  ''Pet ljudi su išli cestom.'' (''Five men/people walked down the street.'')
